          "Created By:"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Rafael was a noble in Casa de Lara in the late 1300s, earning a reputation as a man with dark tastes and an even darker disposition when it came to dealing with enemies (namely any leftover Moorish 'criminals' from the reconquista). Torture is definitely something he was seen taking part in, but even more noteworthy was his pattern of waking late just so that he could keep prisoners awake, often preferring to scare them away from sleep with screeching, screams, and banging on the bars of their cells with anything metallic he could grab and swing with his otherwise spindly arms. \n\nAround Summer 1405, Rafael was walking back to his tower with his attendant knights and a squire when a great shadow descended upon them, inky blackness so cold and dark that it was as though light had never existed in the first place. A nightmare of hope, unreal in the face of this truth. An old and powerful Lasombra embraced him, draining his relatives and servants, then taking a night to explain to him what he'd become. The young, malicious noble was shaken, of course, but saw this as an opportunity to create a legacy of pain and fear. After the Anarch Revolt and subsequent rise of the Sabbat, Rafael went along willingly and happily with the rest of his clan, making war against those most powerful and ancient monsters who'd been manipulating us all in their games.\n\nDuring the late 1800s, he selected one particularly occult minded and sociopathic fellow to attempt embracing. His pride and selfishness prevented him from seeing a point in Embracing a Childe, but finally one had proven himself worthy. After terrorizing him night after night, driving him to the point of breaking, the young man was drained until death, and left in the blackness of pain and empty body for a small time longer than perhaps he should have. Regardless, the vitae took hold, and Gevurah was born. Their relationship has been excellent since then, natural leaders, intelligent and efficient and stubborn.\n\nIn the early 1900s the two followed Crowley for a time, grooming him, and then some shit Malkavian snuck the Embrace right out from their noses. What happened after was a shame. \nMid 1900s Rafael splits for a time and goes to Mexico to reinforce and help teach the Path of Night to younger Lasombra and any who will listen or be coerced.\nLate 1900s Rafael links back up with Gevurah in Miami. Southern sieges happen, and a pack is formed with Ladon, Creep. Al1 is encountered when the Archbishop of LA, Rafael's sire and Gevurah's grandsire, calls for help in Los Angeles."
        ],
        [
